    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-16T06:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-16T06:54:00-05:00" n="711"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0090F/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-16T15:00:00+03:06"
                            >January 16, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. A request was made to the King<note n="2" xml:id="d711fn2">Abdul Aziz ibn
                        Saud, King of Saudi Arabia.</note> on December 15 for permission to put into
                    effect plan for consular representation in Dhahran referred to in Department’s
                    110, November 30, 10 p.m.,<note n="3" xml:id="d711fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1943v04#pg_840">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 840</ref>.</note> and the King referred
                    question to Yusuf Yassin, Acting Foreign Minister.</p>
                <p>No reply has yet been received and I fear that if the matter is pressed now the
                    answer will be no. Minister of Finance<note n="4" xml:id="d711fn4">Shaikh
                        Abdullah Sulaiman.</note> who favors plan suggests that it be left dormant
                    until opportunity occurs for discussing it directly with Amir Faisal.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d711fn5">Second son of the King, Viceroy of the Hejaz, and Saudi
                        Arabian Minister for Foreign Affairs; for correspondence regarding the Amir
                        Faisal’s visit to the United States, from which he was returning at this
                        time, see <ref target="frus1943v04#pg_840">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, pp. 840</ref> ff.</note> Details follow by
                        mail.<note n="6" xml:id="d711fn6">Despatch 92, January 12, not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
